---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { isBlogPublished } from '../../lib/blogGate';
import BlogCrossLinks from '../../components/BlogCrossLinks.astro';
const slug = Astro.url.pathname.replace('/blog/', '').replace(/\/$/, '');
const isPublished = await isBlogPublished(slug);
if (!isPublished) return Astro.redirect('/404');
---
<Layout title="How to Research New Crypto Projects (DYOR Guide)" description="A complete guide to doing your own research on cryptocurrency projects. Learn to evaluate tokenomics, teams, community, and liquidity." keywords="DYOR crypto, research crypto projects, tokenomics analysis, crypto due diligence, evaluate altcoins, crypto research guide">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"How to Research New Crypto Projects (DYOR Guide)","description":"A complete guide to doing your own research on cryptocurrency projects. Learn to evaluate tokenomics, teams, community, and liquidity.","datePublished":"2026-06-16","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"xCrypto24","url":"https://xcrypto24.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"xCrypto24"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://xcrypto24.com/blog/research-new-crypto-projects"}})} />
  <div style="max-width:800px;margin:2rem auto;padding:0 1rem;">
    <nav style="font-size:0.85rem;color:#a1a1aa;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
      <a href="/blog" style="color:#c084fc;text-decoration:none;">← Blog</a> › <span>Altcoins</span>
    </nav>
    <BlogCrossLinks title="How to Research New Crypto Projects (DYOR Guide)" />
    <h1 style="font-size:2rem;font-weight:700;color:#fafafa;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">How to Research New Crypto Projects (DYOR Guide)</h1>
    <div style="font-size:0.85rem;color:#71717a;margin-bottom:2rem;">
      <time datetime="2026-06-16">June 16, 2026</time> · 8 min read
    </div>
    <p style="font-size:1.05rem;color:#d4d4d8;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:2rem;">"Do Your Own Research" is the most repeated advice in crypto — and for good reason. Blindly following influencers or social media hype is the fastest way to lose money. This guide provides a structured framework for evaluating any crypto project, from established protocols to newly launched tokens.</p>

    <!-- Tokenomics -->
    <h2 style="font-size:1.25rem;font-weight:300;color:#c084fc;margin-top:2.5rem;margin-bottom:1rem;border-left:4px solid #8b5cf6;padding-left:1rem;">Evaluate Tokenomics</h2>
    <p style="color:#d4d4d8;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1rem;">Tokenomics — the economic design of a token — determines its long-term value potential. Understanding how tokens are distributed, how supply changes over time, and what creates demand is fundamental to any investment decision.</p>

    <div style="margin:1.5rem 0;display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:1rem;">
      <div style="padding:1rem;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid rgba(139,92,246,0.3);background:rgba(88,28,135,0.15);">
        <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:#e4e4e7;"><span style="color:#a78bfa;font-weight:600;">Total Supply:</span> Is it fixed or inflationary?</p>
      </div>
      <div style="padding:1rem;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid rgba(139,92,246,0.3);background:rgba(88,28,135,0.15);">
        <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:#e4e4e7;"><span style="color:#a78bfa;font-weight:600;">Circulating:</span> What % is already in market?</p>
      </div>
      <div style="padding:1rem;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid rgba(139,92,246,0.3);background:rgba(88,28,135,0.15);">
        <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:#e4e4e7;"><span style="color:#a78bfa;font-weight:600;">Vesting:</span> When do team/VC tokens unlock?</p>
      </div>
      <div style="padding:1rem;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid rgba(139,92,246,0.3);background:rgba(88,28,135,0.15);">
        <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:#e4e4e7;"><span style="color:#a78bfa;font-weight:600;">Utility:</span> What drives demand for the token?</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="margin:1.5rem 0;padding:1.2rem;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid rgba(139,92,246,0.3);background:rgba(88,28,135,0.15);">
      <p style="font-size:0.8rem;font-weight:600;color:#a78bfa;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.05em;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">💡 Key Insight</p>
      <p style="font-size:0.95rem;color:#e4e4e7;">A token with a <span style="color:white;font-weight:500;">low circulating supply relative to total supply</span> means massive future dilution. If only 10% is circulating and 90% unlocks over the next year, selling pressure will be enormous regardless of project quality.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Team -->
    <h2 style="font-size:1.25rem;font-weight:300;color:#c084fc;margin-top:2.5rem;margin-bottom:1rem;border-left:4px solid #8b5cf6;padding-left:1rem;">Research the Team</h2>
    <p style="color:#d4d4d8;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1rem;">The people behind a project are often the strongest indicator of its potential. A strong team with relevant experience and a track record of delivery greatly increases the probability of success.</p>

    <div style="margin:1.5rem 0;padding:1.2rem;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid rgba(139,92,246,0.3);background:rgba(88,28,135,0.15);">
      <p style="font-size:0.8rem;font-weight:600;color:#a78bfa;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.05em;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">🧩 Team Research Steps</p>
      <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.75rem;">
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:0.75rem;">
          <span style="flex-shrink:0;width:1.5rem;height:1.5rem;border-radius:50%;background:rgba(88,28,135,0.5);border:1px solid rgba(139,92,246,0.4);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-size:0.7rem;color:#c084fc;font-weight:700;">1</span>
          <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:#d4d4d8;">Find the founders on LinkedIn — verify their work history</p>
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:0.75rem;">
          <span style="flex-shrink:0;width:1.5rem;height:1.5rem;border-radius:50%;background:rgba(88,28,135,0.5);border:1px solid rgba(139,92,246,0.4);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-size:0.7rem;color:#c084fc;font-weight:700;">2</span>
          <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:#d4d4d8;">Check their GitHub profiles for actual code contributions</p>
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:0.75rem;">
          <span style="flex-shrink:0;width:1.5rem;height:1.5rem;border-radius:50%;background:rgba(88,28,135,0.5);border:1px solid rgba(139,92,246,0.4);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-size:0.7rem;color:#c084fc;font-weight:700;">3</span>
          <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:#d4d4d8;">Look for previous projects — did they deliver or abandon them?</p>
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:0.75rem;">
          <span style="flex-shrink:0;width:1.5rem;height:1.5rem;border-radius:50%;background:rgba(88,28,135,0.5);border:1px solid rgba(139,92,246,0.4);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-size:0.7rem;color:#c084fc;font-weight:700;">4</span>
          <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:#d4d4d8;">Search for interviews or conference talks</p>
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:0.75rem;">
          <span style="flex-shrink:0;width:1.5rem;height:1.5rem;border-radius:50%;background:rgba(88,28,135,0.5);border:1px solid rgba(139,92,246,0.4);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-size:0.7rem;color:#c084fc;font-weight:700;">5</span>
          <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:#d4d4d8;">Check VC backers — reputable funds perform due diligence</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Community -->
    <h2 style="font-size:1.25rem;font-weight:300;color:#c084fc;margin-top:2.5rem;margin-bottom:1rem;border-left:4px solid #8b5cf6;padding-left:1rem;">Assess Community Health</h2>
    <p style="color:#d4d4d8;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1rem;">A strong community indicates genuine interest and long-term staying power. But beware — fake communities with bot followers are easy to manufacture. Quality matters more than quantity.</p>

    <div style="margin:1.5rem 0;display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:1rem;">
      <div style="padding:1rem;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid rgba(34,197,94,0.3);background:rgba(20,83,45,0.1);">
        <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:#e4e4e7;"><span style="color:#4ade80;font-weight:600;">Healthy:</span> Organic discussions, technical questions, constructive criticism allowed</p>
      </div>
      <div style="padding:1rem;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid rgba(239,68,68,0.3);background:rgba(127,29,29,0.1);">
        <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:#e4e4e7;"><span style="color:#f87171;font-weight:600;">Unhealthy:</span> Only price talk, critics banned, bot-like activity</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p style="color:#d4d4d8;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1rem;">Join the project's Discord or Telegram and lurk for a few days. Are people discussing the technology and use cases, or is it purely price speculation? Do the admins engage genuinely with questions?</p>

    <!-- GitHub -->
    <h2 style="font-size:1.25rem;font-weight:300;color:#c084fc;margin-top:2.5rem;margin-bottom:1rem;border-left:4px solid #8b5cf6;padding-left:1rem;">Check GitHub Activity</h2>
    <p style="color:#d4d4d8;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1rem;">For any project claiming to build technology, their GitHub repository tells the real story. Active development with frequent commits, multiple contributors, and meaningful code changes indicates a genuine project.</p>

    <div style="margin:1.5rem 0;padding:1rem;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid rgba(139,92,246,0.3);background:rgba(88,28,135,0.08);">
      <div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;align-items:center;justify-content:center;gap:1.5rem;text-align:center;">
        <div><p style="font-size:1.25rem;font-weight:700;color:#a78bfa;">Weekly</p><p style="font-size:0.75rem;color:#a1a1aa;">Commit frequency (good)</p></div>
        <div><p style="font-size:1.25rem;font-weight:700;color:#a78bfa;">5+</p><p style="font-size:0.75rem;color:#a1a1aa;">Active contributors</p></div>
        <div><p style="font-size:1.25rem;font-weight:700;color:#a78bfa;">Open</p><p style="font-size:0.75rem;color:#a1a1aa;">Source code visible</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="margin:1.5rem 0;padding:1.2rem;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid rgba(139,92,246,0.3);background:rgba(88,28,135,0.15);">
      <p style="font-size:0.8rem;font-weight:600;color:#a78bfa;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.05em;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">💡 Pro Tip</p>
      <p style="font-size:0.95rem;color:#e4e4e7;">Look at the <span style="color:white;font-weight:500;">quality of commits</span>, not just quantity. Some projects pad their count with trivial changes. Meaningful development shows new features, bug fixes, and architectural improvements.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Liquidity -->
    <h2 style="font-size:1.25rem;font-weight:300;color:#c084fc;margin-top:2.5rem;margin-bottom:1rem;border-left:4px solid #8b5cf6;padding-left:1rem;">Analyze Liquidity and Trading</h2>
    <p style="color:#d4d4d8;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1rem;">Liquidity determines how easily you can buy or sell without significantly moving the price. Low liquidity means high slippage and makes you vulnerable to manipulation. Our tracker displays real-time liquidity data for assessment before trading.</p>

    <div style="margin:1.5rem 0;display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:1rem;">
      <div style="padding:1rem;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid rgba(139,92,246,0.3);background:rgba(88,28,135,0.15);">
        <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:#e4e4e7;"><span style="color:#a78bfa;font-weight:600;">Depth:</span> Can you sell $10K+ without major slippage?</p>
      </div>
      <div style="padding:1rem;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid rgba(139,92,246,0.3);background:rgba(88,28,135,0.15);">
        <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:#e4e4e7;"><span style="color:#a78bfa;font-weight:600;">Volume:</span> Is daily trading consistent?</p>
      </div>
      <div style="padding:1rem;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid rgba(139,92,246,0.3);background:rgba(88,28,135,0.15);">
        <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:#e4e4e7;"><span style="color:#a78bfa;font-weight:600;">Exchanges:</span> Listed on reputable platforms?</p>
      </div>
      <div style="padding:1rem;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid rgba(139,92,246,0.3);background:rgba(88,28,135,0.15);">
        <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:#e4e4e7;"><span style="color:#a78bfa;font-weight:600;">Lock:</span> Is LP locked and for how long?</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Holder Distribution -->
    <h2 style="font-size:1.25rem;font-weight:300;color:#c084fc;margin-top:2.5rem;margin-bottom:1rem;border-left:4px solid #8b5cf6;padding-left:1rem;">Check Holder Distribution</h2>
    <p style="color:#d4d4d8;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1rem;">Use block explorers to check how tokens are distributed. A healthy project shows gradual organic growth in unique holders, with no single entity controlling an outsized portion of supply.</p>

    <div style="margin:1.5rem 0;padding:1rem;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid rgba(139,92,246,0.3);background:rgba(88,28,135,0.08);">
      <div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;align-items:center;justify-content:center;gap:1.5rem;text-align:center;">
        <div><p style="font-size:1.25rem;font-weight:700;color:#a78bfa;">1,000+</p><p style="font-size:0.75rem;color:#a1a1aa;">Unique holders (minimum)</p></div>
        <div><p style="font-size:1.25rem;font-weight:700;color:#a78bfa;">&lt; 5%</p><p style="font-size:0.75rem;color:#a1a1aa;">Max per wallet</p></div>
        <div><p style="font-size:1.25rem;font-weight:700;color:#a78bfa;">Growing</p><p style="font-size:0.75rem;color:#a1a1aa;">Holder count trend</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="margin:1.5rem 0;padding:1.2rem;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid rgba(139,92,246,0.3);background:rgba(88,28,135,0.15);">
      <p style="font-size:0.8rem;font-weight:600;color:#a78bfa;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.05em;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">💡 Use Our Tracker</p>
      <p style="font-size:0.95rem;color:#e4e4e7;">Our crypto tracker shows <span style="color:white;font-weight:500;">real-time holder data, liquidity metrics, and market cap</span> for thousands of tokens — giving you the data points you need without jumping between multiple tools.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <div style="margin-top:2.5rem;padding:1.2rem;background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(139,92,246,0.1),rgba(109,40,217,0.05));border:1px solid rgba(139,92,246,0.3);border-radius:12px;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:1rem;">
      <p style="color:#c084fc;font-size:0.9rem;font-weight:500;">🪙 Track crypto in real-time with our free tool</p>
      <a href="/coins" style="padding:0.5rem 1.2rem;background:linear-gradient(180deg,#a78bfa,#7c3aed);color:white;border-radius:6px;text-decoration:none;font-size:0.85rem;font-weight:600;">Open Tracker →</a>
    </div>
    <div style="margin-top:2rem;text-align:center;">
      <a href="/blog" style="color:#71717a;font-size:0.85rem;text-decoration:none;">← Back to all articles</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
